There are only 13 dolphins in the group that move actively in the shallow bay of Nan'ao. The bay will do its utmost to keep the white elves thriving. About 'Journeys in Nature': Guangdong Nan'ao Series Nan'ao Island in Guangdong Province is a rare habitat of greenery on the Tropic of Cancer. In June, the southeastern monsoon brings warm, moist air to the island, nurturing all lives: from ancient fig trees to newborn black-naped terns, from mysterious undersea creatures to medical herbs, which bestow Nan'ao Island with many stories. For more: Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 1: Windy Island Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 2: Reef Ninja Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 3: Brown-winged Dancer Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 4: Black-naped Tern Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 5: Living with Tides Guangdong Nan'ao Series | Episode 6: Wind in the Sea (Cover is a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)